In the below JSON Object, there are 2 properties, namely, nodes & links. 
The nodes properties is an array of all data items with name as key vaue pair.

The Links properties is again array of link with properties, 
-source -- source is the index of data item in the Nodes array
-target -- target is the index of data item in the Nodes array
-value -- just for description -keep it 100 for now

eg: nodes: [ {"name":"Viren" }, {"name":"Peeyush"},{"name": "Tauseef"}]

So for creating a link from Viren(Array index 0) -> Peeyush(Array index 1) -> Tauseef(array index 2), links array should have 2 objects as links:[
    {"source":0, "target":1},
    {"source":1, "target":2}
]



